{
  "stem": "8842.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Her parents started to get very close to my parents.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And her brother fell in love with my sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And believe it or not, they got married while we were still in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had another brother and another additional member in the family in the same little room.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this is how their wedding was in that little room.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was their honeymoon in together with the parents and sisters.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You can imagine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But always made a joke-- my father was a big joker-- always made a joke on every thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He used to say, now get out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The young couple has to be there alone for a while.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we used to stay outside and wait.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] This was-- but that was a normal.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were young, but we were so old at this point already.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We knew everything that could be to make our lives easier and, and happier for a moment, if possible.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We tried to help each other.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I would say that the worst impact of life to me, personally, was the day that they came to take all the children away from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was an Aktion that destroyed actually me at this point, because I have seen how they did it and what they did to these kids.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They came in with trucks and dogs-- big German shepherd dogs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they went from house to house and screamed whoever has little kids to come outside.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they didn't take the mother and the child together.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They just tore out the baby, or a child of four or five or 10 and threw them into those trucks.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
